ional and interdisciplinary work in this book contributes to this moment by analyzing how borders are experienced by migrants and borderlanders in South Asia, how mobility and diaspora are engaged in literature and media, and how the lives of migrants are transformed during their journey to new homes in South Asia, the Middle East, North America, and Europe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBorderlandszSouth Asia. 0aSouth Asian diaspora. 0aSouth AsianszForeign countries. 4aAsian Studies. 4aInterdisciplinary Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aBorders, Mobility, South Asia, Diaspora, Migration.1 aAmin, Rohullah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyle, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChakraborty, Ananya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerdoush, Md. Azmeary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerdoush, Md. Azmeary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarris, Tina.1 aJones, Reece, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Reece, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMeeteren, Masja van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRahman, Mirza Zulfiqur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRajagopalan, Kavitha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRasel, Azizul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator